    "details": "Trifecta Tech Foundation reports:\n\n> With Defaults targetpw (or Defaults rootpw) enabled, the password of\n> the target account (or root account) instead of the invoking user is\n> used for authentication. sudo-rs prior to 0.2.10 incorrectly recorded\n> the invoking user's UID instead of the authenticated-as user\\'s UID in\n> the authentication timestamp. Any later sudo invocation on the same\n> terminal while the timestamp was still valid would use that timestamp,\n> potentially bypassing new authentication even if the policy would have\n> required it.\n",
    "id": "FreeBSD-2025-0387",
